  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Chase debit card, here are the steps you should take:\n\n1. Immediately contact Chase\n- Call the Chase customer service number: 1-800-935-9935\n- For international collect calls: 1-713-262-3300\n\n2. Report the card as lost or stolen\n- Chase will cancel your current card\n- They will issue a new debit card\n- Prevent unauthorized transactions on your account\n\n3. Check your recent transactions\n- Review your account for any suspicious charges\n- Report any unauthorized transactions to Chase\n\n4. Update automatic payments\n- Since you'll get a new card number, update any recurring payments or subscriptions\n\n5. Consider temporarily freezing your card\n- You can do this through the Chase mobile app or online banking\n- This prevents anyone from using the card until you decide what to do\n\n6. If you find the original card later\n- Do not use it, as it has been deactivated\n- Destroy the old card\n\nOptional steps:\n- Monitor your credit report\n- Set up transaction alerts on your account\n\nChase recommends acting quickly to protect your account and prevent potential fraud.",
